%parsesuit splits up a string into 4 suits, which we can now do as we please with
\newcommand{\parsesuit}[1]{%
\StrBefore{#1}{,}[\raws]%
\StrBetween[1,2]{#1}{,}{,}[\rawh]%
\StrBetween[2,3]{#1}{,}{,}[\rawd]%
\StrBehind[3]{#1}{,}[\rawc]%
}
